## Dead Ends
Considered relaxing the 8-item Finding Qualification gate (criteria 1
"meaningfully impacts" and 5 "author would likely fix" are the severity/
subjective screens §2.7 warns about). Decided AGAINST gutting the gate: those
criteria are mostly validity/scope guards (don't flag pre-existing, no
speculation, not intentional changes) and changing them is a behavioral redesign
beyond a prompting-style update (Chesterton's Fence). Instead implemented §2.7
purely in the Quantity guidance: among findings that pass the gate, don't
self-suppress for severity/confidence — coverage-first, lead filters. This is
the safe, in-scope application.

